-- Sydney Water Signs $105 Million Agreement for Plant Improvements
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-12-07T17:35:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-07/sydney-water-signs-105-million-agreement-for-plant-improvements.html
Sydney Water,  Australia ’s largest
water utility, signed a A$100 million ($105 million) service
agreement with  Schneider Electric  and Thompson Controls to
upgrade systems and increase efficiencies at 33 water and
wastewater treatment plants.  Sydney Water, owned by the New South Wales government, also
said it’s spending almost $15 million to improve a wastewater
pumping station and enlarge Narellan’s water treatment system.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
